direct_enhancements.reason: Both methods add items to the comparator's set of known objects, but 'addAsEqual' specifically adds an item as equal to an existing one.
The 'add' method populates the map used by the 'compare' method for ordering comparisons.
Both methods involve checking the locked state of the comparator and throw an exception if locked.
Both methods modify the internal state of the comparator, affecting how it handles unknown objects.
Both methods interact with the comparator's behavior settings, though 'getUnknownObjectBehavior' only retrieves the setting.
